        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 25 at 2:57PM PDT by NWS Sacramento CA</headline>
        <description>At 257 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
East Shore, or 8 miles southeast of Chester, moving west at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Chester, Prattville, Lake Almanor Country Club, Lake Almanor West,
Lake Almanor Peninsula, Hamilton Branch, Canyondam, Lake Almanor,
East Shore, Almanor, and Greenville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
